The paper deals with optimization problems related to data summarization and machine learning, which are typically studied in the subfield of data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also presents novel formulations and anti-concentration inequalities, which are relevant to the fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computational complexity (cs.CC), and computational geometry (cs.CG).
